
[1]pneumatical

   PNEUMATICAL, a. numat'ic. [Gr. breath, spirit; to breathe or blow.]

   1. Consisting of air, as a thin compressible substance; opposed to
   dense or solid substances.

   The pneumatic substance being, in some bodies, the native spirit of the
   body.

   2. Pertaining to air, or to the philosophy of its properties; as
   pneumatic experiments; a pneumatic engine.

   3. Moved or played by means of air; as a pneumatic instrument of music.
     __________________________________________________________________

